      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Dyan Zaslowsky's ''Between Fire and Water in Idaho'' Sept. 10) referred to her raft guide, Taz. In the world of river guides, there can be only one.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Dyan Zaslowsky's ''Between Fire and Water in Idaho'' Sept. 10) referred to her raft guide, Taz. In the world of river guides, there can be only one.</p>
        <p>Last October, my husband and I enjoyed a rafting trip through the Santa Elena Canyon in Big Bend National Park in Texas. Our guide? Taz. She demonstrated the same competence and cool-headedness on that trip as she did guiding the author and her family down the Middle Fork of the Salmon River during the threat of fire.</p>
        <p>I wondered where Taz would spend the summer.</p>
        <p>JEANETTE RUSSELL  Fair Oaks Ranch, Tex.</p>
      </block>
